{{Infobox University |name = Institute of Indonesian Arts and Culture, Bandung |native_name = |image_name = |image = |image_size = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |tagline = |established = {{Start date|1968}} |type = State university |staff = |faculty = |president = |provost = |principal = |rector = Dr. Hj. Een Herdiani, S.Sen., M.Hum |chancellor = |vice_chancellor = |dean = |head_label = |head = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |profess = |city = [[Bandung]] |state = [[West Java]] |country = [[Indonesia]] |coor = |campus = |free_label = |free = |colors = |colours = |mascot = |fightsong = |nickname = ISBI Bandung |affiliations = |footnotes = |website = {{URL|www.isbi.ac.id}} |address = Jalan Buah Batu No. 212 {{flagicon|Indonesia}} |logo = [[File:Isbi bandung.jpg]] |publictransit = }}
'''Institute of Indonesian Arts and Culture, Bandung''' ({{lang-id|Institut Seni Budaya Indonesia Bandung}}, abbreviated as '''ISBI Bandung'''), is a state, arts and cultural-oriented educational institution located in [[Bandung]], [[Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://isbi.ac.id/index.php/visi-misi-dan-tujuan|title=Tentang ISBI Bandung|website=www.isbi.ac.id|accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref>
==History== It was founded in 1968, replacing ''Dance Conservatory'' and ''Bandung Academy of Indonesian Dance''. It became the first and only arts institution in [[Bandung]], [[Indonesia]].
==International Student Admissions == The institute allows foreigners who are interested in learning Indonesian traditional arts and culture to enroll directly as an international student or exchange student.
