The '''Primary Mathematics World Contest''' or '''PMWC''' takes place every year in [[Hong Kong]]. It was first held in 1997, and is sponsored by the [[Po Leung Kuk]] organization. The competition has attracted teams from around the world. Each team consists of 4 members, all of whom must be 13 or younger as of September 1, and must not be enrolled in a secondary institution (or the equivalent).{{Fact|date=August 2007}}
However, the 13th '''Primary Mathematics World Contest''' (2009) was canceled due to the [[WHO]] declaring the [[Influenza A virus subtype H1N1]] a pandemic. A similar event occurred in the 7th '''Primary Mathematics World Contest''' (2003) where the committee postponed the contest to November 2003 due to [[SARS]]. The PMWC committee provides room and board at the Panda Hotel in [[Tsuen Wan]].




